-- Berkshire’s Shaw Opens China Factory in Nantong, to Employ 250
-- B y   M a r c i   J a c o b s
-- 2013-09-13T12:15:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-09-13/berkshire-s-shaw-opens-china-factory-in-nantong-to-employ-250.html
Shaw Industries Group, the carpet
maker owned by  Warren Buffett ’s Berkshire Hathaway Inc., opened a
210,000-square-foot (20,000-square-meter) plant in Nantong,
China, to expand sales in the world’s most populous nation.  The plant is expected to employ 250 people at full capacity,
the unit of Omaha, Nebraska-based Berkshire said today in a
statement distributed by Business Wire.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Marci Jacobs in New York at 
